## Workflow

Bobby uses a ticket-based workflow with these stages:

```
0-ideas → 1-backlog → 2-ready-for-refinement → 3-ready-for-development
→ 4-in-progress → 5-peer-review → 6-ready-for-testing
→ 7-ready-for-release → 10-released
```

Side tracks: `8-needs-rework`, `9-blocked`

## Roles

### Engineer (work-tickets skill)
When told to "work tickets", load the `work-tickets` skill from `.claude/skills/work-tickets/SKILL.md`. This skill handles:
- Picking up tickets from `3-ready-for-development`
- TDD red-green-refactor cycle
- Running health checks before/after changes
- Moving tickets through the pipeline

### QE (qe skill)
When told to "test tickets" or "QE", load the `qe` skill from `.claude/skills/qe/SKILL.md`. This handles:
- Testing tickets in `6-ready-for-testing`
- Browser-based verification
- Writing QE notes with evidence

### Peer Reviewer (peer-review skill)
When told to "review tickets" or "peer review", load the `peer-review` skill from `.claude/skills/peer-review/SKILL.md`.

### Refiner (refine-tickets skill)
When told to "refine tickets", load the `refine-tickets` skill from `.claude/skills/refine-tickets/SKILL.md`.

### Release Engineer (release-tickets skill)
When told to "release tickets", load the `release-tickets` skill from `.claude/skills/release-tickets/SKILL.md`.

### Ideator (ideate skill)
When told to "ideate" or "brainstorm", load the `ideate` skill from `.claude/skills/ideate/SKILL.md`.

## Learnings

Each skill has a `learnings.md` file that accumulates anti-patterns and best practices discovered during development. Always check the learnings file before starting work — it contains hard-won wisdom from past mistakes.

## Bobby CLI Commands

```
bobby create -t "Title" --type bug -p high   # Create ticket
bobby list                                    # Show board
bobby start TKT-001                          # Pick up ticket
bobby review TKT-001                         # Submit for review
bobby approve TKT-001                        # QE approve
bobby release TKT-001                        # Ship it
bobby retro TKT-001 "pattern name"           # Create retrospective
bobby learn work-tickets "pattern" "desc"    # Add learning
```
